The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for segmenting and classifying retinal arterioles and venules on fundus images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep convolutional neural networks and InceptionV4 modules suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the importance of accurately measuring disease severity, which could be related to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of retinal fundus images suggests a potential connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
